  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 662de8a6992c486fa87e377ee9253765, type: 3}
  m_Name: Bridge Integration
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Trailback.Demo.Features.Data.FeatureDemoData
  featureName: Bridge Integration
  shortDescription: Keep application code separate from Trailback-specific implementation
    details.
  fullDescription: 'Trailback supports an optional bridge-based integration approach
    that helps keep navigation code isolated from the rest of your application.


    Instead
    of calling Trailback directly from multiple systems, application code communicates
    through a dedicated integration layer. This keeps navigation-related logic in
    one place and makes it easier to change or extend navigation behavior over time.


    A
    bridge can also reduce the impact of framework changes. If navigation requirements
    evolve or parts of the integration need to be replaced, most application code
    can remain unchanged because it depends on the bridge rather than Trailback directly.


    For
    teams that prefer a simpler setup, direct framework access remains available
    and can be used without introducing an additional integration layer.'
  screenshots: []
  videoUrl: 
  documentationUrl: https://github.com/akpardeshi/Trailback-Unity/#quick-start--build-your-first-trailback-integration
